&nbsp;
<h3><strong>Ruthenium in Industry and Electronics</strong></h3>
The mid-20th century witnessed Ruthenium's integration into various industrial processes. Its remarkable resistance to corrosion made it an invaluable component in the production of wear-resistant electrical contacts and electrodes. Ruthenium's ability to withstand harsh conditions found applications in electronics, elevating its status from a laboratory curiosity to an essential element in the manufacturing sector.

