<h3><strong>Catalyzing Change: Ruthenium in Chemistry</strong></h3>
Ruthenium's catalytic properties emerged as a focal point of scientific exploration in the latter half of the 20th century. Chemists began to harness its catalytic prowess to expedite various chemical reactions, contributing to the synthesis of essential compounds. Ruthenium-based catalysts found applications in the production of ammonia, pharmaceuticals, and even in the refinement of petroleum.

&nbsp;
<h3><strong>The Spark of Innovation: Ruthenium in Electronics and Beyond</strong></h3>
