&nbsp;
<h3><strong>8. Tungsten in Electronics</strong></h3>
The latter half of the 20th century saw tungsten carve a niche for itself in the electronics industry. Tungsten's high melting point and stability made it an ideal material for thin films and wiring in semiconductors. As electronic devices became smaller and more complex, tungsten's contributions to the world of microelectronics became increasingly vital.

